title: Understanding ETL
text: ETL is an acronym used in data warehousing. It involves three major processes to facilitate the management and transformation of data between different storage systems.

title: The 'Extract' Process
text: The first step in ETL is 'Extract', meaning to retrieve data from different sources that might be in varied formats.

title: The 'Transform' Process
text: The 'Transform' step involves modifying the data to fit the operational needs or analytical purposes, potentially involving cleaning or restructuring.

title: The 'Load' Process
text: The 'Load' phase of ETL is where transformed data gets written into the target system, usually a data warehouse or database.
